  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Transportation for a Rural Orphanage in Costa Rica</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Children from Hogarcito San Ramon orphanage currently walk 45 minutes each way to/from public school daily, regardless of weather, on a two-lane road without sidewalks.  Children who require medical treatment are transported by taxi to facilities that are often an hour away, and the orphanage relies on donations to cover these transportation costs.The amount of money needed to purchase a vehicle is far beyond their means.</narrative>
  </description>
